    ResourceBase

    public class ResourceBase
extends org.graphity.server.model.impl.QueriedResourceBase
implements com.hp.hpl.jena.ontology.OntResource, ContainerResource, MatchedIndividual
    Base class of generic read-write Graphity Processor resources. Configured declaratively using sitemap ontology to provide Linked Data layer over a SPARQL endpoint. Supports pagination on containers (implemented using SPARQL query solution modifiers).
    Author:
    Martynas Juseviƒçius
    See Also:
    ContainerResource, OntResource, 15 Solution Sequences and Modifiers

      • ResourceBase

        public ResourceBase(@Context
            javax.ws.rs.core.UriInfo uriInfo,
            @Context
            org.graphity.server.model.SPARQLEndpoint endpoint,
            @Context
            com.hp.hpl.jena.ontology.OntClass ontClass,
            @Context
            javax.ws.rs.core.Request request,
            @Context
            javax.servlet.ServletContext servletContext,
            @Context
            javax.ws.rs.core.HttpHeaders httpHeaders,
            @Context
            com.sun.jersey.api.core.ResourceContext resourceContext)
        Public JAX-RS constructor. Suitable for subclassing. If the request URI does not match any URI template in the sitemap ontology, 404 Not Found is returned. If the matching ontology class is a subclass of LDP Page, this resource becomes a page resource and HATEOS metadata is added (relations to the container and previous/next page resources).
        Parameters:
        uriInfo - URI information of the current request
        endpoint - SPARQL endpoint of this resource
        ontClass - matched ontology class
        request - current request
        servletContext - webapp context
        httpHeaders - HTTP headers of the current request
        resourceContext - resource context
